When JIRA deletes information from the tables it uses the DELETE statement (it needs to be like this) and the DELETE statement does not release the table space (Oracle default behaviour), JIRA supports Oracle so it would be good if it ensure the table space is indeed freed by issuing an "ALTER TABLE <tablename> SHRINK SPACE;"

